HEADWORD: Lymphated
<hw>Lymph"a*ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lymphatus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>lymphare</ets> to water, dilute with water, to drive out of
one's senses, to make mad.]</ety> <def>Frightened into madness;
raving.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

